                                                                                             NIST SP 800-213                                             GUIDANCE FOR THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT
                                                                                                                                           ESTABLISHING IOT DEVICE CYBERSECURITY REQUIREMENTS

                                                                                                                Glossary

                                                                                              Capabilities         Comprehensive list of device cybersecurity capabilities derived from
                                                                                              Catalog              analysis of comprehensive list of source documents for the application or
                                                                                                                   sector. For the federal sector, NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5 [800-53] provided
                                                                                                                   the definition of controls used to create the NIST-generated capabilities
                                                                                                                   catalog used for the Federal profile.

                                                                                              Configuration        The possible conditions, parameters, and specifications with which an
                                                                                              [800-128,            information system or system component can be described or arranged.
                                                                                              Adapted]             The Device Configuration capability does not define which configuration
This publication is available free of charge from: https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-213




                                                                                                                   settings should exist, simply that a mechanism to manage configuration
                                                                                                                   settings exists.
                                                                                              Core Baseline        A set of technical device capabilities needed to support common
                                                                                                                   cybersecurity controls that protect the customer’s devices and device data,
                                                                                                                   systems, and ecosystems.
                                                                                              Customer             The organization or person that receives a product or service.
                                                                                              [ISO9000]
                                                                                              Device               Cybersecurity features or functions that computing devices provide through
                                                                                              Cybersecurity        their own technical means (i.e., device hardware and software).
                                                                                              Capability
                                                                                              Device               See core baseline.
                                                                                              Cybersecurity
                                                                                              Capability Core
                                                                                              Baseline
                                                                                              Device Identifier    A context-unique value—a value unique within a specific context—that is
                                                                                              [800-56A,            associated with a device (for example, a string consisting of a network
                                                                                              Adapted]             address).
                                                                                              Entity               A person, device, service, network, domain, manufacturer, or other party
                                                                                                                   who might interact with an IoT device.
                                                                                              Federal Profile      Profile of the IoT device cybersecurity capability core baseline [IR8259A]
                                                                                                                   and non-technical supporting capability core baseline [IR8259B] to provide
                                                                                                                   security guidance provided to federal government organizations related to
                                                                                                                   IoT devices.
                                                                                              Interface            A boundary between the IoT device and entities where interactions take
                                                                                              [CNSSI,              place. There are two types of interfaces: network and local.
                                                                                              Adapted]
                                                                                              Local Interface      An interface that can only be accessed physically, such as a port (e.g.,
                                                                                                                   USB, audio, video/display, serial, parallel, Thunderbolt) or a removable
                                                                                                                   media drive (e.g., CD/DVD drive, memory card slot).




